{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 On the morphisms of slice and coslice categories\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Given a base category \u55349?\u56478?, and some set {\i A} we wish to study the homsets of the slice (resp. coslice) category \u55349?\u56478?{\sub {\i A}} (resp. \u55349?\u56478?{\super {\i A}}. {\b These homsets might be empty, or have more than one element.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We remind that slice categories consider {\i morphisms to A} as their {\i objects} (written as ({\i Z},\u8198?{\i \u966?}) for any {\i \u966?}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i Z}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i A}), while coslice categories consider {\i morphisms from A} as their {\i objects} (written as ({\i \u966?},\u8198?{\i Z}) for any {\i \u966?}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i Z}. {\i Morphisms}, of the form {\i \u963?}{\sub {\i A}}\u8196?:\u8196?({\i Z}{\sub 1},\u8198?{\i \u966?}{\sub 1})\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?({\i Z}{\sub 2},\u8198?{\i \u966?}{\sub 2}) (resp. {\i \u963?}{\super {\i A}}\u8196?:\u8196?({\i \u966?}{\sub 1},\u8198?{\i Z}{\sub 1})\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?({\i \u966?}{\sub 2},\u8198?{\i Z}{\sub 2})) in a slice category \u55349?\u56478?{\sub {\i A}} (resp. coslice category \u55349?\u56478?{\super {\i A}}) map such objects to one another if and only if there exists a morphism in \u55349?\u56478? (the base category!) such that {\i \u966?}{\sub 1}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u966?}{\sub 2}{\i \u963?} (resp. {\i \u963?}{\i \u966?}{\sub 1}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u966?}{\sub 2}).\par}
